      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear that, but isn't there a risk that sticking strictly to what people thought in the 1700s makes the Constitution outdated or even dangerous in a modern context? like, if the law can't adapt to how much more lethal guns are now, isn't the \"originalist\" view itself a form of activism because it's forcing an old framework onto a new reality?",
