      "content": "You are absolutely right to point out that rigid originalism can appear dangerous when applied to modern realities like high-capacity magazines or assault rifles, which the Founders never envisioned. However, critics of the current Court's approach argue that the \"living constitution\" method is actually the true form of judicial activism because it allows judges to impose their personal moral views on the law rather than adhering to the text. The current Court's strict adherence to historical evidence is seen as a necessary check against the judiciary overstepping its bounds by rewriting the Constitution to fit modern political agendas.",
